China Stocks: Chalco Gains, China Minsheng Banking Advances

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-08-17T07:50:14Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-16/beiqi-foton-china-coal-huaxin-cement-china-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in  China  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the 3 p.m. close.  The Shanghai Composite Index, which tracks the bigger of
China’s stock exchanges, fell 0.3 percent to 2,601.26. The  CSI
300 Index (SHSZ300)  lost 0.4 percent to 2,886.01.  Developers: China Vanke Co. (000002 CH), the nation’s
largest developer, sank 1.7 percent to 8.22 yuan. Poly Real
Estate Group Co. (600048 CH) slipped 0.4 percent to 11.05 yuan.  China’s housing ministry is studying measures to
“eliminate” speculation in the  property market  so it can
return to a “normal and rational” order, Shanghai Securities
News reported today, citing an unidentified person.  Train makers: CSR Corp. (601766 CH), the nation’s largest
train maker, lost 2 percent to 5.38 yuan. China CNR Corp.
(601299 CH) declined 2 percent to 4.92 yuan.  China will suspend the operation and construction of high-
speed rail lines if there are significant safety risks, China
National Radio reported yesterday, citing Vice Premier Zhang
Dejiang.  Beiqi Foton Motor Co. (600166 CH), China’s biggest
commercial-vehicle maker, retreated 2.1 percent to 8.36 yuan.
The company sold 42,317 vehicles in July, compared with 51,669 a
year ago, according to a company statement to the  Shanghai Stock
Exchange .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
